      "content": "When he asks for more detailed feedback, it's best to keep your response brief and consistent with your initial message. You can offer very general, high-level guidance, such as suggesting he focus on gaining more hands-on experience with [mention a specific cloud service your company uses, e.g., AWS Lambda or Azure Functions]. Always pivot the conversation back to the fact that the hiring decision is final, which is a professional boundary you must maintain. This avoids getting pulled into a drawn-out debate about the specific technical gap.",
      "source": "target",
